e\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.084438925797501e-35, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1115}, {\"ngram\": \"theembodiment\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1143}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It combined landmarks like the Eiffel Tower and key figures from French history, such as Marie Antoinette, with cultural, musical and fashion representations of modern France.\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1342, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1232, \"end\": 1246, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French history\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1256, \"end\": 1272, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.532486303755351e-34, \"text\": \"Marie Antoinette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\"}, {\"begin\": 1335, \"end\": 1341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9860950365109685, \"rank\": 0.012043315481778536, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"It combined landmarks\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1188}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1210}, {\"ngram\": \"key figures\", \"from\": 1215, \"to\": 1226}, {\"ngram\": \"cultural, musical and fashion representations\", \"from\": 1279, \"to\": 1324}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These included surfers, rappers and members of LGBTQ+ communities.\", 