m\": \"anthems\", \"from\": 4190, \"to\": 4197}, {\"ngram\": \"other national symbols\", \"from\": 4202, \"to\": 4224}, {\"ngram\": \"no government or state officials\", \"from\": 4241, \"to\": 4273}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The exclusion of Russia has led to speculation that its agents may have been responsible for a series ofrailway sabotagesthat caused significant travel disruption on the opening day of the Games.\", \"from\": 4294, \"to\": 4489, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4311, \"end\": 4317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999989175922965, \"rank\": 1.0822869352656358e-06, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The exclusion\", \"from\": 4294, \"to\": 4307}, {\"ngram\": \"speculation\", \"from\": 4329, \"to\": 4340}, {\"ngram\": \"its agents\", \"from\": 4346, \"to\": 4356}, {\"ngram\": \"a series ofrailway\", \"from\": 4387, \"to\": 4405}, {\"ngram\": \"sabotagesthat\", \"from\": 4406, \"to\": 4419}, {\"ngram\": \"significant travel disruption\", \"from\": 4427, \"to\": 4456}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening day\", \"from\": 4460, \"to\": 4475}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 4479, \"to\": 4488}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Though nobody was hurt or killed, such attacks undermine public confidence, impose economic and social costs on people, and were clearly an attempt to tarnish the image of France.\", \"from\": 4490, \"to\": 4669, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4662, \"end\": 4668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9860950365109685, \"rank\": 0.012043315481778536, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nobody\", \"from\": 4497, \"to\": 4503}, {\"ngram\": \"such attacks\", \"from\": 4524, \"to\": 4536}, {\"ngram\": \"public confidence\", \"from\": 4547, \"to\": 4564}, {\"ngram\": \"economic and social costs\", \"from\": 4573, \"to\": 4598}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 4602, \"to\": 4608}, {\"ngram\": \"an attempt\", \"from\": 4627, \"to\": 4637}, {\"ngram\": \"the image\", \"from\": 4649, \"to\": 4658}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France has a long-held reputation for successfully delivering numerous major events each year.\", \"from\": 4671, \"to\": 4765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4671, \"end\": 4677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9860950365109685, \"rank\": 0.012043315481778536, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a long-held reputation\", \"from\": 4682, \"to\": 4704}, {\"ngram\": \"numerous major events\", \"from\": 4733, \"to\": 4754}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, there was alsodisruptionat the Uefa Champions League final in 2022, which was being staged at the Stade de France (the main Olympic venue this summer).\", \"from\": 4766, \"to\": 4926, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Stade de France\", \"from\": 4869, \"to\": 4888}, {\"ngram\": \"the main Olympic venue\", \"from\": 4890, \"to\": 4912}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many Liverpool supporters were put through a traumatising experience when entering the stadium, and riot police teargassed spectators while failing to protect them from being attacked by local thugs.\", \"from\": 4927, \"to\": 5126, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4932, \"end\": 4941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liverpool_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.9940085230301458, \"rank\": 0.006027590277187619, \"text\": \"Liverpool\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liverpool_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liverpool_F.C.\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a traumatising experience\", \"from\": 4970, \"to\": 4995}, {\"ngram\": \"the stadium\", \"from\": 5010, \"to\": 5021}, {\"ngram\": \"riot police\", \"from\": 5027, \"to\": 5038}, {\"ngram\": \"spectators\", \"from\": 5050, \"to\": 5060}, {\"ngram\": \"local thugs\", \"from\": 5114, \"to\": 5125}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This followed Paris quickly stepping in to stage the match after Uefa removed St Petersburg'sright to host the gamefollowing Russia's invasion of Ukraine.\", \"from\": 5128, \"to\": 5282, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5142, \"end\": 5147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.477388917670513e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 5253, \"end\": 5259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999989175922965, \"rank\": 1.0822869352656358e-06, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 5274, \"end\": 5281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999999985620889, \"rank\": 1.4285872879034597e-09, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the match\", \"from\": 5177, \"to\": 5186}, {\"ngram\": \"Uefa\", \"from\": 5193, \"to\": 5197}, {\"ngram\": \"St\", \"from\": 5206, \"to\": 5208}, {\"ngram\": \"the gamefollowing\", \"from\": 5235, \"to\": 5252}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Whether these events were another deliberate attempt to diminish France or just a coincidence remains debatable.\", \"from\": 5283, \"to\": 5395, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5348, \"end\": 5354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9860950365109685, \"rank\": 0.012043315481778536, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these events\", \"from\": 5291, \"to\": 5303}, {\"ngram\": \"another deliberate attempt\", \"from\": 5309, \"to\": 5335}, {\"ngram\": \"just a coincidence\", \"from\": 5358, \"to\": 5376}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some have suggested that Russia's president, Vladimir Putin, has wanted toundermine the IOCfor much of the past decade.\", \"from\": 5397, \"to\": 5516, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5422, \"end\": 5428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999989175922965, \"rank\": 1.0822869352656358e-06, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 5442, \"end\": 5456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0415954126373348e-31, \"text\": \"Vladimir Putin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the past decade\", \"from\": 5500, \"to\": 5515}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He sees it as a western institution governed by values and rules that maintain a dominance he resents.\", \"from\": 5517, \"to\": 5619, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a western institution\", \"from\": 5531, \"to\": 5552}, {\"ngram\": \"values\", \"from\": 5565, \"to\": 5571}, {\"ngram\": \"rules\", \"from\": 5576, \"to\": 5581}, {\"ngram\": \"a dominance\", \"from\": 5596, \"to\": 5607}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As such, Russia has been planning to host the World Friendship Games a little more than a month after the Paris Olympics finishes.\", \"from\": 5621, \"to\": 5751, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5630, \"end\": 5636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999989175922965, \"rank\": 1.0822869352656358e-06, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the World Friendship Games\", \"from\": 5663, \"to\": 5689}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics finishes\", \"from\": 5723, \"to\": 5750}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While there is some confusion over whether the event will bepostponed to 2025, there are claims that more than 100 nations have already committed to participating in what may ultimately come to pose an existential threat to the modern Olympic movement.\", \"from\": 5752, \"to\": 6004, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some confusion\", \"from\": 5767, \"to\": 5781}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 5795, \"to\": 5804}, {\"ngram\": \"claims\", \"from\": 5841, \"to\": 5847}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 100 nations\", \"from\": 5853, \"to\": 5874}, {\"ngram\": \"an existential threat\", \"from\": 5951, \"to\": 5972}, {\"ngram\": \"the modern Olympic movement\", \"from\": 5976, \"to\": 6003}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC normally does its utmost to control the places and spaces that it selects to host Olympic events, whether that means suppressing displays of activism, preventing acts of terrorism, or even minimising the commercial intrusion of brands that have no legal right to associate with the event.\", \"from\": 6006, \"to\": 6302, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6010, \"end\": 6013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1630988473845512e-31, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its utmost\", \"from\": 6028, \"to\": 6038}, {\"ngram\": \"the places\", \"from\": 6050, \"to\": 6060}, {\"ngram\": \"spaces\", \"from\": 6065, \"to\": 6071}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic events\", \"from\": 6096, \"to\": 6110}, {\"ngram\": \"displays\", \"from\": 6143, \"to\": 6151}, {\"ngram\": \"activism\", \"from\": 6155, \"to\": 6163}, {\"ngram\": \"acts\", \"from\": 6176, \"to\": 6180}, {\"ngram\": \"terrorism\", \"from\": 6184, \"to\": 6193}, {\"ngram\": \"the commercial intrusion\", \"from\": 6214, \"to\": 6238}, {\"ngram\": \"brands\", \"from\": 6242, \"to\": 6248}, {\"ngram\": \"no legal right\", \"from\": 6259, \"to\": 6273}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 6292, \"to\": 6301}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, such is the currently fractious nature of local and global geopolitics that we should expect more controversy before the Olympic flame in Paris is finally extinguished.\", \"from\": 6304, \"to\": 6481, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6451, \"end\": 6456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.477388917670513e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the currently fractious nature\", \"from\": 6321, \"to\": 6351}, {\"ngram\": \"local and global geopolitics\", \"from\": 6355, \"to\": 6383}, {\"ngram\": \"more controversy\", \"from\": 6406, \"to\": 6422}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic flame\", \"from\": 6430, \"to\": 6447}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2010-2026,The Conversation Media Group Ltd\", \"from\": 6483, \"to\": 6537, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2010-2026,The Conversation Media Group Ltd\", \"from\": 6483, \"to\": 6537}]}]}"